# Formatting Standards

## Word (.docx) Standards

### Typography
- Body text: Times New Roman, 13pt
- Heading 1: Times New Roman Bold, 16pt, UPPERCASE
- Heading 2: Times New Roman Bold, 14pt
- Heading 3: Times New Roman Bold Italic, 13pt
- Table text: Times New Roman, 11pt
- Footer/Header: Times New Roman, 10pt

### Layout
- Paper: A4 (210mm x 297mm)
- Margins: Left 3cm, Right 2cm, Top 2cm, Bottom 2cm
- Line spacing: 1.5
- Paragraph spacing: 6pt after
- Heading numbering: 1. / 1.1. / 1.1.1. format
- Page numbers in footer (center)
- Document title in header (right-aligned)

### Tables
- All borders visible (single line, 0.5pt)
- Header row: bold, dark blue background (#1F4E79), white text
- Alternating row colors: white / light gray (#F2F2F2)
- Cell padding: 2mm all sides
- Text alignment: left for text, right for numbers, center for headers

### Table of Contents
- Auto-generated from headings
- Include H1, H2, H3 levels
- Right-aligned page numbers with dot leaders

### Images
- Max width: 15cm (within margins)
- Centered horizontally
- Caption below: italic, 10pt, "Hình X.Y: Description"
- 6pt spacing before and after

## Excel (.xlsx) Standards

### Header Row
- Font: Calibri Bold, 11pt
- Background: dark blue (#1F4E79)
- Text color: white
- Frozen panes: freeze top row
- Auto-filter enabled

### Data Formatting
- Body font: Calibri, 11pt
- Currency: #,##0 VND or $#,##0.00
- Dates: dd/mm/yyyy
- Percentages: 0.0%
- Numbers: #,##0 (thousands separator)
- Negative numbers: red text

### Layout
- Column widths: auto-fit with minimum 12 characters
- Row height: auto-fit with minimum 20px
- Sheet names: descriptive, no special characters, max 31 chars
- Print area: set for all data ranges
- Page setup: landscape for wide tables, portrait for narrow

### Formulas
- Prefer formulas over hardcoded values
- Use named ranges for complex references
- Color conventions: blue text for input cells, black for formulas
- Validate no #REF!, #DIV/0!, #VALUE!, #NAME? errors

### Conditional Formatting
- Red background for negative values
- Green background for positive targets met
- Yellow background for warnings/near-threshold

## PowerPoint (.pptx) Standards

### Slide Layout
- Dimensions: 16:9 widescreen (33.867cm x 19.05cm)
- Consistent margins: 1.5cm all sides

### Typography
- Title font: Calibri Bold, 28pt
- Subtitle: Calibri, 20pt
- Body text: Calibri, 18pt
- Bullet points: Calibri, 16pt
- Footnotes: Calibri, 10pt
- Maximum 6 bullet points per slide
- Maximum 8 words per bullet

### Slides Structure
- Title slide: company logo, title, subtitle, date, author
- Agenda slide (slide 2)
- Content slides
- Q&A / Thank You slide (last)
- Slide numbers in footer (all slides except title)

### Images & Diagrams
- Centered on slide
- Maximum 80% of slide area
- Minimum 20px padding from edges
- Caption below if needed: 12pt, italic

### Speaker Notes
- Required for every content slide
- Include talking points, data sources, context
- No more than 200 words per slide

## Review Tracking Standards

### Word (.docx) Review Tracking

1. **Inline Comments** at changed/added content:
   - Format: "[PHASE N] [Author/Model] - [Description]"
   - Example: "[PHASE 1] Steve/Opus 4.6 - Created from input/requirements.pdf page 3"

2. **Highlighted Changed Text**:
   - NEW text: LIGHT GREEN highlight (#E2EFDA)
   - MODIFIED text: YELLOW highlight (#FFF2CC)
   - TEMPLATE text (unchanged): no highlight

3. **Section-Level Update Markers** (REVIEW version only):
   - After each section heading, add italic gray text (9pt):
     "Updated by [Author] using [Model] on [Date] | Phase [N]"

4. **Change Log Page** (last page before appendix):
   - Table: Section | Change Type | Description | Author | Model | Date
   - Change types: NEW, MODIFIED, REFORMATTED, FIXED
   - Summary row at top: "Total: X new, Y modified, Z fixes"

### Excel (.xlsx) Review Tracking

1. **Audit Columns** (rightmost 3 columns of every data sheet):
   - _Status: NEW / MODIFIED / UNCHANGED / FIXED
   - _Change_Desc: what changed in this row
   - _Updated_By: Author / Model / Date

2. **Row Color Coding**:
   - GREEN (#E2EFDA): NEW rows
   - YELLOW (#FFF2CC): MODIFIED rows
   - WHITE: UNCHANGED rows

3. **_Change_Log Sheet** (separate sheet):
   - Columns: Sheet | Cell/Row | Change Type | Old Value | New Value | Description | Author | Date
   - Summary at top: "Total: X new rows, Y modified cells, Z formula updates"

4. **Cell Comments** on modified cells:
   - "[Author/Model] Changed from '[old]' to '[new]' - [reason]"

### PowerPoint (.pptx) Review Tracking

1. **Speaker Notes Change Tracking** (prepended to notes):
   ```
   --- CHANGES (Phase N) ---
   [Author] / [Model] / [Date]
   - Added: [what]
   - Modified: [what]
   - Source: [input file]
   ---
   [actual speaker notes follow]
   ```

2. **Slide Footer Annotation** (REVIEW version only):
   - Small text (8pt, gray) at bottom-left of modified slides:
     "Modified by [Author] | Phase [N] | [Date]"

3. **Change Summary Slide** (last slide before Q&A):
   - Title: "Document Change Log"
   - Table: Slide # | Change Type | Description | Author | Date

### Dual-Version Output

Every output file has TWO versions:
- `filename_REVIEW.ext` - Full tracking for internal review
- `filename.ext` - Clean for client delivery

Agent creates REVIEW version first, then runs strip_tracking.py for CLEAN version.
